Package: fireR
Title: Download and Load USGS Fire Data (MTBS and SE FireMap)
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Noah", "Weidig", email = "noah.weidig@ufl.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides fast, convenient access to USGS fire datasets.
    For MTBS (Monitoring Trends in Burn Severity), downloads the composite
    burned-area extent shapefile and returns it as either an 'sf' or 'terra'
    SpatVector object with optional filtering by year and incident type.
    For the Southeast FireMap (SE FireMap) Annual Burn Severity Mosaics,
    downloads per-year ZIP archives of predicted Composite Burn Index (CBI)
    values (0-3) covering 78 ARD Landsat tiles across the southeastern
    United States for years 2000-2022.
